            <title>Description</title>
            <paragraph><strong>PolygonOccluder3D</strong> stores a polygon shape that can be used by the engine's occlusion culling system. When an <reference internal="True" refuri="class_occluderinstance3d#class-occluderinstance3d"><inline classes="std std-ref">OccluderInstance3D</inline></reference> with a <strong>PolygonOccluder3D</strong> is selected in the editor, an editor will appear at the top of the 3D viewport so you can add/remove points. All points must be placed on the same 2D plane, which means it is not possible to create arbitrary 3D shapes with a single <strong>PolygonOccluder3D</strong>. To use arbitrary 3D shapes as occluders, use <reference internal="True" refuri="class_arrayoccluder3d#class-arrayoccluder3d"><inline classes="std std-ref">ArrayOccluder3D</inline></reference> or <reference internal="True" refuri="class_occluderinstance3d#class-occluderinstance3d"><inline classes="std std-ref">OccluderInstance3D</inline></reference>'s baking feature instead.</paragraph>
            <paragraph>See <reference internal="True" refuri="class_occluderinstance3d#class-occluderinstance3d"><inline classes="std std-ref">OccluderInstance3D</inline></reference>'s documentation for instructions on setting up occlusion culling.</paragraph>
